gov.usgs.anss.smgetter

Class FetchListBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.smgetter.FetchListBuilder

  • public final class FetchListBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    This class will get a list of stations where strong motion fetches are desired, and for each call to buildFetchList with a event location (Mw, lat, long, and depth) will create a fetchlist entry appropriate for all stations close enough to the station. The constructor builds an array list of Station object (an inner class) from various NEIC databases. This list is then use to evaluate what fetchlist entries to create for all submitted events. NOTE: this fetchlist is bigger than the fetchlist for the StongMotionBuilder since it will gather any station within 110 km of a quake regardless of PGA.

    The policy for getting a station is :
    1) If <110 km (1 deg), always get a SM record
    2) if %gt 900 km, never get a SM record
    3) if >110 and < 900, for all stations at dist=190*Mag-415 away, get a record

    The time area to get is the origin time + first arrival time from TauP, -60 seconds. All requests are for 3 minutes. The EIDSListener calls an instance of this to process the events its gets in.

        evaluate a earthquake against the list and create fetches for the criteria. Save it if it has a PGA above 0.01 g and, nothing > 900 km, 2) everything < 110, 3) -415*190*Mw elsewhere @param net The network of the net id
